4. Non-Functional Requirements (NFR)
1.	Availability: System shall be available 99.9% of the time.
2.	Response Time: Pages must load in under 2 seconds.
3.	Concurrency: System must support 500 concurrent users.
4.	Mobile-First: The UI must be fully responsive for mobile devices.
5.	Data Encryption: All user passwords must be hashed using bcrypt.
6.	SSL: All data transmission must be over HTTPS.
7.	Database Backup: Daily backups of the database must be performed.
8.	Scalability: System should be deployable via Docker for easy scaling.
9.	Usability: A new user should be able to post an item in under 3 minutes.
10.	Privacy: User phone numbers must remain hidden unless the user chooses to share them.
11.	Maintainability: Code must follow PEP8 (if Python) or Airbnb Style Guide (if JS).
12.	Recoverability: System must recover from a crash within 15 minutes.
13.	Accessibility: The site must meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards (for color contrast).
14.	Audit Trail: All admin actions must be logged.
15.	Browser Compatibility: Must support Chrome, Firefox, and Safari.
16.	Search Efficiency: Database queries for searches must be indexed.
17.	File Size Limit: Images must be compressed to under 2MB before storage.
18.	Session Timeout: Idle users should be logged out after 30 minutes.
19.	Test Coverage: Backend code must have at least 80% unit test coverage.
20.	Localization: Date formats must adapt to the user's region (DD/MM/YYYY).

b.Acceptance Criteria
1.Availability:
System uptime must be at least 99.9% per month.
Total downtime must not exceed 43 minutes per month.
2.Response Time:
95% of pages must load in under 2 seconds.
No request should take longer than 4 seconds.
3.Concurrency:
System must support at least 500 concurrent users.
Resource usage (CPU/Memory) must remain below 80% under load.
4.Mobile-Firsta:
UI must function correctly on screens as small as 320px.
No horizontal scrolling should be required.
5.Data Encryption:
100% of user passwords must be hashed using bcrypt.
No passwords should be stored in plain text.
6.SSL:
All data must be transmitted over HTTPS.
All HTTP requests must be automatically redirected to HTTPS.
7.Database Backup:
Backups must be performed every 24 hours.
Data must be restorable within 10 minutes.
8.Scalability:
System must be deployable using Docker without code changes.
New instances must be scalable within 5 minutes.
9.Usability:
90% of new users must be able to post an item within 3 minutes.
The posting process must not exceed 5 steps.
10.Privacy:
User phone numbers must be hidden by default.
No unauthorized exposure of user data is allowed.
11.Maintainability:
Code must fully follow PEP8 or Airbnb Style Guide.
Code reviews must show no critical issues.
12.Recoverability:
System must recover from crashes within 15 minutes.
Data loss must not exceed 5 minutes.
13.Accessibility:
Must comply with WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards.
Users must be able to navigate using a keyboard.
14.Audit Trail:
All admin actions must be logged.
Logs must be stored for at least 30 days.
15.Browser Compatibility:
System must function correctly on Chrome, Firefox, and Safari.
No critical bugs allowed on these browsers.
16.Search Efficiency:
Search results must be returned within 1 second.
All search queries must use indexed fields.
17.File Size Limit:
Images must be compressed to under 2MB.
Upload must be rejected if file exceeds 5MB before compression.
18.Session Timeout:
Users must be logged out after 30 minutes of inactivity.
A warning must be shown 5 minutes before logout.
19.Test Coverage:
Backend code must have at least 80% unit test coverage.
All tests must pass without errors.
20.Localization:
Date formats must adapt to the user’s region.
Localization must be automatically detected.


5. Application Specifications (How the system is built technically)
a. Architecture
Frontend (Client-side):
Built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It provides the user interface where users can submit lost/found items, search, and navigate through the system.
Backend (Server-side):
Handles business logic such as user authentication, post creation, matching algorithm, and notifications.
Database:
Stores user data, posts, messages, and system logs.

b. Database Model
1.Users:
id (Primary Key)
email (Unique)
password
phone
profile_image
2.Posts:
id (Primary Key)
user_id (Foreign Key → Users)
title
description
category
location
status (Lost/Found/Resolved)
image
3.Messages:
id (Primary Key)
sender_id (FK → Users)
receiver_id (FK → Users)
message_text
timestamp
4.Reports:
id (Primary Key)
post_id (FK → Posts)
reason
5.Relationships:
One user can create many posts
Each post belongs to one user
Messages connect two users
Each report is linked to one post

c. Technologies Used
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
→ Chosen for simplicity and responsiveness
Backend: Python/Django
→ Used for handling logic, authentication, and APIs
Database: SQLite
→ Efficient data storage and querying

d. User Interface Design
1.Top Bar & Header:
Contains login links and navigation (Submit Lost Item, Submit Found Item, View Posts)
2.Hero Section (Main Area):
Form for submitting lost/found items
Input fields for item name and location
Buttons for submitting posts
3.Process Section:
Displays step-by-step instructions on how the system works
4.Industries Section:
Shows categories like airport, hotel, taxi, restaurant, etc.
5.Footer:
Contains contact info, links, and social media

e. Security Measures
1.Authentication:
Users must log in using email and password
2.Password Encryption:
Passwords are hashed using bcrypt before storage
3.HTTPS (SSL):
All data is transmitted securely
4.Access Control:
Only authorized users can edit or delete their posts
Admins have special permissions
5.Data Privacy:
Sensitive information (like phone numbers) is hidden unless shared
6.Session Management:
Users are automatically logged out after inactivity

